ructure used by the lookup, then update the lookup itself, and finally the constant. \n   Database entity \n Next, update the data structure  Status  \\  Status  to  TaskStatus  \\  TaskStatus , meaning both the data structure and its entity must be renamed. \n After that, review the lookups referencing this entity and update their underlying data structures accordingly. \n Finally, update the screen sections related to  Status  (now  TaskStatus ) and  Task , as well as all screens where these sections are used. \n Renamed fields in screen sections should be removed and added again. Besides adjusting names and labels, remember to update any associated lookups. \n In the screens, you must also reset the correct  DataMember  and  DataSource  values in the  Data  section located under the  Properties  tab. \n After completing the updates, the dependencies may look like this: \n  \n\n\n[Image: https://community.origam.com/uploads/default/original/2X/2/2ea702a15e1c7585be388665443a56bc23627740.png]\nDescription: The image displays a user interface section that lists entities and their types related to a data service or application context. On the left side under \u0022Found In,\u0022 the listed items include: \u0022OrigamEntity2Id,\u0022 \u0022TaskStatus,\u0022 \u0022TaskStatus_Name_GetId,\u0022 and \u0022TaskStatus_New.\u0022 On the right side under \u0022Root Type,\u0022 the corresponding types are shown: \u0022Virtual Entity,\u0022 \u0022Database Entity,\u0022 \u0022Data Service Lookup,\u0022 and \u0022Data Constant.\u0022 The purpose of this UI component appears to be for managing or displaying data entity definitions and their classifications within a system.\n\n\n  \n  \n\n\n[Image: https://community.origam.com/uploads/default/original/2X/5/5f11e4b138365cc1e635b9dd4a5a6a0678544731.png]\nDescription: The image displays a section labeled \u0022Found In\u0022 which lists various components related to a data entity or structure. The items include: \u0022Lookup TaskStatus_Name_GetId\\Status\u0022 categorized as a Data Structure, \u0022Task\\ref\\TaskStatusId\u0022 as a Database Entity, \u0022TaskStatus\u0022 classified as a Screen Section, and \u0022TaskStatus\\TaskStatus\u0022 also noted as a Data Structure. The \u0022Root Type\u0022 column indicates the type classification for each item presented. The context suggests a technical documentation or user interface environment related to data management or database design.\n\n\n  \n   Other model elements \n Some dependencies are indirect and therefore not visible in the dependency/reference search. Examples include: \n \n Menu screen reference \u2014 rename  Status  to  Task Status  \n Roles \u2014 create a new role  FRM_TaskStatus  instead of renaming the existing  FRM_Status  \n Application roles in the client application \u2014 assign the new role(s) to users \n \n After updating all these elements, you may reach the end of the process. If the application runs without errors and all related screens function correctly, the renaming was successful. \n If issues persist, you will need to  fix all existing errors . \n   Conclusion \n After completing this tutorial, you should have a clear understanding of what is involved in renaming entities or fields. \n Recognizing the complexity of the process may encourage you to avoid such changes in production projects. However, experimenting in a test project can provide valuable insight into how ORIGAM works \u2014 particularly how the model elements are interconnected and how they relate to the database. \n In some cases, it may ultimately be easier to rebuild certain parts from scratch rather than rename existing elements.","vector_provider":"AI.Ollama.OllamaTextEmbeddingGenerator","vector_generator":"__","last_update":"2026-05-01T23:58:40"},"vector":[-0.0058836057,-0.023209887,-0.049124334,0.022007234,-0.024450611,-0.049433257,0.035430446,-0.007757521,-0.005388521,0.0003849129,-0.00031645503,-0.02327103,-0.014514155,0.05584692,0.001168799